==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[wærloga|wǣrloga]]'', from ''[[wær|wǣr]]'' ‘promise’ (from Indo-European ''*wēr-'' ‘true’; compare ''[[veritable]]'') + ''[[loga]]'' ‘liar’, from ''[[leogan|lēogan]]'' ( > English ''[[lie]]''); the ending in ''-ck'' is from Scottish & Northern English.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈwɔːlɒk/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{obsolete}} A [[traitor]] or oath-breaker.
# {{obsolete}} The [[Devil]], [[Satan]]; a [[demon]].
# (''originally Scotland and Northern UK'') A man in league with the Devil; a male magic-user, a [[wizard]].

